President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 1, 2015, as Loyalty Day in the United States. In his proclamation, he emphasizes that Americans are united by a set of shared ideals and unalienable rights, such as freedom, justice, and equality. He believes in the power of democracy and opportunity, and encourages citizens to work towards bettering the country. The President acknowledges the struggles and triumphs throughout American history, highlighting the courage of patriots and the ongoing journey to perfect the Union. He calls for self-criticism and the recognition that change depends on our actions, attitudes, and values. Loyalty Day is meant to recognize the American spirit of loyalty and the sacrifices made for the nation. The President calls upon all Americans to support this national observance by displaying the flag or pledging allegiance to the Republic.